entries.meaning: One who stays on the sidelines; a spectator or nonparticipant.
examples: The result is more dissent because successful collective action sustains the involvement of old participants while convincing sideliners of the usefulness of protest and ensuring their future participation  […]

entries.meaning: (US) A beekeeper, neither a hobbyist nor a fully-fledged commercial operator, for whom beekeeping is a secondary source of income.
